credit.credit-words: Nor is the least a cheerful heart, That tastes those gifts with joy.
3. Ten thousand precious gifts My daily thanks employ;
5. Through all eternity, to Thee A joyful song I'll raise:
But O, eternity's too short To utter all Thy praise!

direction-type.words: 4. O, how can words with equal warmth
That glows within my raptured heart?—
But Thou canst read it there.
